The paper discusses a triple extraction system for constructing a knowledge graph from domain-specific text. This involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and databases (cs.DB). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
